Variables in Python
==========================
variable is a container for some value(integer,string,float..etc)

declare a variable
--------------------
myVariableName ---this is the convention which is followed for variable

myVariable = 30 
myVariable

MyVariable --- python is a case sensitive language and this will throw an error 



myVariable + 34 
myVariable **3
value=input("Enter the value:")
Enter the value:50

value
'50'
value +20 
it will give an error because '50' is a string and whenever a value is in '' it is a string 

and input function takes value as string 


To Convert value from string to an integer we have to use cast 

value  = int(input("Enter the value: ")) ---  to cast value as int
Enter the value:60
value
60

value  = float(input("Enter the value: ")) --- to cast value as float 



