How to use string in python program
============================================================================================
a='I am a single quoted string'
b="I am a double quoted string"
c="""I am a triple quoted string"""

print(a)
print(b)
print(c)


a='I am a \single quoted string don\'t'  -----'\' escape character 
b="I am a \double \"quoted string"
c="""I am a \triple \"quoted string"""

print(a)
print(b)
print(c)



a='I am a \\single quoted string don\'t'  -----'\' escape character 
b="I am a \\double \"quoted string"
c="""I am a \\triple \"quoted string"""

print(a)
print(b)
print(c)



a='I am a \\single quoted string don\'t'  -----'\' escape character 
b="I am a \\double \"quoted string"
c="""I am a \\triple \"quoted string"""

print(len(a))
print(b)
print(c)




